It‚Äôs been almost three decades since the rage virus escaped a biological weapons laboratory, and now, still in a ruthlessly enforced quarantine, some have found ways to exist amidst the infected. One such group of survivors lives on a small island connected to the mainland by a single, heavily-defended causeway. When one of the group leaves the island on a mission into the dark heart of the mainland, he discovers secrets, wonders, and horrors that have mutated not only the infected but other survivors as well.

snippet.title: Canada election 2025: English language leaders' debate | FULL
snippet.description:
Liberal Leader Mark Carney sought to cast himself as a safe choice to guide Canada through a crisis during the English-language debate on Thursday evening.

Carney, currently leading in the polls, was the primary target during the final debate of the election, with his chief rival Conservative Party Leader Pierre Poilievre trying to paint him as ‚Äúmore of the same‚Äù following a decade of Liberal leadership.

‚ÄúMr. Carney, Justin Trudeau‚Äôs staffers are actually here with you at this debate in Montreal, writing the talking points that you are regurgitating into the microphone,‚Äù he said.

Carney, who tried to differentiate himself from former prime minister Justin Trudeau, retorted: ‚ÄúLook, I do my own talking points thank you.‚Äù

Later in the debate, NDP Leader Jagmeet Singh accused Carney of failing to defend Canadian jobs threatened by U.S. tariffs.

Bloc Quebecois Leader Yves-Francois Blanchet, meanwhile, argued that Carney must disclose his financial assets to show he‚Äôs better than Trudeau, picking up on an issue that has dogged Carney throughout the campaign.

00:00 Group photo
7:51 Debate begins
8:39 Tariffs and threats to Canada
26:07 Affordability and the cost of living
44:47 Public safety and security
1:04:02 Energy and climate
1:21:48 Leading in a Crisis

snippet.title: What I Saw in Antarctica
snippet.description:
A big thank you to FUTURE of SPACE and their Media Team for capturing and contributing stunning visuals from this extraordinary voyage.

FUTURE of SPACE is a media/production company dedicated to creating original content, immersive programs, and experiential events that explore new frontiers, celebrate the human experience, and elevate global conversations. Through groundbreaking initiatives like Space2Sea, FoS connects diverse voices to inspire curiosity, innovation, and a more connected future.

Media Team Credit:  Brendan Hall, Gabriella Canal, Tyler Brower

Follow FUTURE of SPACE for more visionary content and experiences ahead:
Website: https://futureofspace.io 
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/futureofspace.io/
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/people/futureofspaceio/61566710741346/
YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@FUTUREofSPACE_official

What does Neil deGrasse Tyson do on a trip to Antarctica? On this special episode, Neil deGrasse Tyson recounts his trip to Antarctica, where he walked with penguins, crossed the Drake Passage, and took a deep-sea dive into the alien Antarctic waters.

snippet.title: Inside Lenny Kravitz‚Äôs Regal Paris Home | Open Door | Architectural Digest
snippet.description:
Today, AD is welcomed by Lenny Kravitz to tour his regal home in Paris. The superstar musician has loved Paris since he first visited in 1989 but it wasn‚Äôt until the early 2000s that he decided it was time to get a place in the city. With a small apartment on the Seine in mind, Kravitz's vision deviated a little when he ended up viewing the grand mansion of Countess Anne d‚ÄôOrnano. Having started his AD100 studio, Kravitz Design, Lenny spearheaded the design of his home. Soulful elegance was Kravitz‚Äôs design philosophy, filling his home with photographs, artwork, and artifacts connecting him to his ancestors and influential figures from throughout his life. However, the true heart and soul of the house lies downstairs in the boiler room Kravitz converted into his own speakeasy-style club.

See more of the musician's Paris home: https://www.architecturaldigest.com/gallery/inside-lenny-kravitzs-paris-refuge

We set out to tackle one of Australia‚Äôs toughest 4WD tracks ‚Äî Six Stage. üî• A brutal 1km climb with six of the gnarliest challenges you‚Äôll find. It‚Äôs been a dream of Shauno‚Äôs for years‚Ä¶ but he‚Äôs never attempted it, until now‚Ä¶

What started as a mission to reach a speccy camp has quickly turned into a night run rescue mission, with a busted rig halfway up and no way out under its own steam. 

This track isn‚Äôt for the faint-hearted‚Ä¶ If you‚Äôre not twin locked & on 35s, don‚Äôt even bother. But we‚Äôve taken the turnoff & the boys are frothing for what‚Äôs ahead. 

Shaun, Graham, Jock, & Jesse - formerly with 4WD Action - have been delivering the best off-road content in Australia for 20+ years. From epic car builds & 4x4 tips to exploring iconic spots like Fraser Island, Utah, The Kimberley, Colorado, The Rubicon Trail & The Simpson Desert, we create content for every off-roader. We left 1 4WD on the track... Our 24hr rescue mission.

We set out to tackle one of Australia‚Äôs toughest 4WD tracks ‚Äî Six Stage. üî• A brutal 1km climb with six of the gnarliest challenges you‚Äôll find. It‚Äôs been a dream of Shauno‚Äôs for years‚Ä¶ but he‚Äôs never attempted it, until now‚Ä¶

What started as a mission to reach a speccy camp has quickly turned into a night run rescue mission, with a busted rig halfway up and no way out under its own steam. 

This track isn‚Äôt for the faint-hearted‚Ä¶ If you‚Äôre not twin locked & on 35s, don‚Äôt even bother. But we‚Äôve taken the turnoff & the boys are frothing for what‚Äôs ahead. 

Shaun, Graham, Jock, & Jesse - formerly with 4WD Action - have been delivering the best off-road content in Australia for 20+ years. From epic car builds & 4x4 tips to exploring iconic spots like Fraser Island, Utah, The Kimberley, Colorado, The Rubicon Trail & The Simpson Desert, we create content for every off-roader. We've even hit the tracks with the legends from Donut Media! Whether you‚Äôre rocking a fully modified Toyota LandCruiser or just getting started with your Hilux or Ranger, we‚Äôve got you covered for all things 4WD and adventure.

id.title: Kami meninggalkan 1 4WD di lintasan... misi penyelamatan 24 jam kami
id.description:
Kami meninggalkan 1 4WD di lintasan... Misi penyelamatan 24 jam kami.

Kami berangkat untuk menaklukkan salah satu lintasan 4WD terberat di Australia ‚Äî Six Stage. üî• Pendakian brutal sejauh 1 km dengan enam tantangan terberat yang akan Anda temukan. Itu adalah impian Shauno selama bertahun-tahun... tetapi dia tidak pernah mencobanya, sampai sekarang...

Apa yang dimulai sebagai misi untuk mencapai perkemahan khusus telah dengan cepat berubah menjadi misi penyelamatan malam hari, dengan rig yang rusak di tengah jalan dan tidak ada jalan keluar dengan sendirinya.

Lintasan ini bukan untuk orang yang lemah hati... Jika Anda tidak terkunci ganda & menggunakan 35, jangan repot-repot. Tetapi kami telah mengambil jalan keluar & para lelaki bersemangat untuk apa yang ada di depan.

Shaun, Graham, Jock, & Jesse - sebelumnya dengan 4WD Action - telah memberikan konten off-road terbaik di Australia selama 20+ tahun. Dari pembuatan mobil epik & tips 4x4 hingga menjelajahi tempat-tempat ikonik seperti Fraser Island, Utah, The Kimberley, Colorado, The Rubicon Trail & The Simpson Desert, kami membuat konten untuk setiap pengendara off-road. Kami bahkan telah menjelajahi trek dengan para legenda dari Donut Media! Baik Anda menggunakan Toyota LandCruiser yang dimodifikasi sepenuhnya atau baru saja memulai dengan Hilux atau Ranger, kami siap membantu Anda untuk semua hal yang berhubungan dengan 4WD dan petualangan.

en.title: We left 1 4WD on the track... our 24hr rescue mission
en.description:
We left 1 4WD on the track... Our 24hr rescue mission.

We set out to tackle one of Australia‚Äôs toughest 4WD tracks ‚Äî Six Stage. üî• A brutal 1km climb with six of the gnarliest challenges you‚Äôll find. It‚Äôs been a dream of Shauno‚Äôs for years‚Ä¶ but he‚Äôs never attempted it, until now‚Ä¶

What started as a mission to reach a speccy camp has quickly turned into a night run rescue mission, with a busted rig halfway up and no way out under its own steam. 

This track isn‚Äôt for the faint-hearted‚Ä¶ If you‚Äôre not twin locked & on 35s, don‚Äôt even bother. But we‚Äôve taken the turnoff & the boys are frothing for what‚Äôs ahead. 

Shaun, Graham, Jock, & Jesse - formerly with 4WD Action - have been delivering the best off-road content in Australia for 20+ years. From epic car builds & 4x4 tips to exploring iconic spots like Fraser Island, Utah, The Kimberley, Colorado, The Rubicon Trail & The Simpson Desert, we create content for every off-roader. We've even hit the tracks with the legends from Donut Media! Whether you‚Äôre rocking a fully modified Toyota LandCruiser or just getting started with your Hilux or Ranger, we‚Äôve got you covered for all things 4WD and adventure.

snippet.title: GRIZZLIES at WARRIORS | #SoFiPlayIn | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | April 15, 2025
snippet.description:
The Golden State Warriors defeated the Memphis Grizzlies, 121-116. Stephen Curry (37 points, 8 rebounds, 4 assists) and Jimmy Butler III (38 points, 7 rebounds, 6 assists) combine for 75 points to lead the Warriors to the win. Despite the loss, Desmond Bane totaled 30 points (5 3PM) while Ja Morant added 22 points. The Warriors clinch the #7 seed and will face the #2 Houston Rockets while the Grizzlies will face the winner of the #9 seed Kings and #10 seed Mavericks on Friday for the #8 seed in the Western Conference.

snippet.description:

What would happen to the Earth if the Sun suddenly switched off? is probably the single most popular question submitted to What If.

What If? The Video Series is the official adaptation of the What If? books by Randall Munroe and is produced by Neptune Studios LLC. 

Randall Munroe is the author of the New York Times bestsellers What If? 2, How To, What If?, and Thing Explainer; the science question-and-answer blog What If?; and the popular web comic xkcd (https://xkcd.com). A former NASA roboticist, he left the agency in 2006 to draw comics on the internet full time.

snippet.title: China Hits Back: TikTok, Boeing & Rare Earths in US Trade War | Vantage with Palki Sharma | N18G

China is no longer playing defence in the trade war‚Äîit‚Äôs going after American consumers, brands, and technology. Chinese factories are flooding TikTok with factory-price videos targeting US shoppers and mocking Western brands. There once flew a pilot, high and free

‚ÄúI am your child,
You are my mother and I‚Äôm sitting here dying‚Äù
I say ‚ÄúI got no children, I am but a boy, you are mistaken

to the edge of the forgotten seas‚Äù
‚ÄúSave me from the hurt‚Äù

Deadstick
Death wish

Death wish

Being forced to land

Death wish

Blues skies are turning a darker grey

Death wish

Mayday! Mayday! Mayday! Save me!
I‚Äôm in a tight spot
Catastrophe

I‚Äôm ‚Äòbout to make a crash landing

Deadstick
Deadstick
I‚Äôm a bird with a broken wing
Deadstick
Deadstick
This nightingale can‚Äôt sing
Yeah!

Deadstick
Death wish
I can‚Äôt believe we made it out alive
Deadstick
Death wish
Send me help before I die

snippet.title: Vice President JD Vance drops Ohio State's national championship trophy at White House event
snippet.description:
Ohio State, who won the title in January after navigating the first 12-team College Football Playoff, will be the sport‚Äôs first champion to make the traditional visit since Donald Trump's return to the presidency for a second term.

The last time Ohio State's football team visited the White House to celebrate a playoff championship was in 2015 when former President Barack Obama was in office.

snippet.title: Rory McIlroy‚Äôs Final Round | Every Single Shot | The 2025 Masters
snippet.description:
Every single shot from every single hole of 2025 Masters Champion Rory McIlroy's Final Round. #themasters

---

Since 1934, the Masters Tournament has been home to some of golf‚Äôs greatest moments. Amidst blooming azaleas, towering pines and flowering dogwoods, the first full week of April ushers in a stage unique to golf and to sport. Over four days and 72 holes, the smallest field in major championship golf competes for a chance to capture the Green Jacket and a place in Masters history.

Hey ya'll! After years of reacting to your wildest stories, dramatic Reddit posts, and the internet‚Äôs most chaotic moments ‚Äî it‚Äôs time for a bit of a shift. This channel has been such a fun ride, but I‚Äôve been feeling like it‚Äôs time for something more. A new chapter. A fresh vibe.

In this video, I‚Äôm opening up about the future of the Charlotte Dobre channel ‚Äî what‚Äôs staying, what‚Äôs changing, and where we‚Äôre going next. Whether you‚Äôve been here since day one or just found the chaos recently, I‚Äôm so grateful you‚Äôre part of this community. üíú

Change can be scary, but it can also be really freaking exciting. Let‚Äôs take this next step together.

Subscribe if you haven‚Äôt already and drop your thoughts in the comments ‚Äî I want to hear from you!

#charlottedobre #channelupdate #announcementvideo #newchapter #youtubedirection #charlottedobrereacts #thankyoucommunity #creatorupdate #bignews

snippet.description:
Eureka! It‚Äôs a new series of #Taskmaster! Your five volatile elements are Fatiha El-Ghorri, Jason Mantzoukas, Mathew Baynton, Rosie Ramsey and Stevie Martin - plus, of course, a compound of Daviesium and Horneium.

Thursday 1st May at 9pm on Channel 4 and 2nd May around the world on YouTube. üß™

------------

Watch full episodes in the UK on http://Channel4.com
Buy Taskmaster merch: https://taskmasterstore.com/

------------

In this Broadcast Award-winning, BAFTA and Emmy Award-nominated entertainment show, Taskmaster tyrant Greg Davies (Man Down, Cuckoo), with the help of his loyal assistant Alex Horne (The Horne Section and the show‚Äôs creator), sets out to test the wiles, wit and wisdom of five hyper-competitive comedians.

Comedians that have risked life, limb, and dignity in the hope of making the Taskmaster proud so far include: Frank Skinner (The Frank Skinner Show), Mel Giedroyc (The Great British Bake Off), Romesh Ranganathan (Asian Provocateur), Hugh Dennis (Outnumbered), Sally Phillips (Bridget Jones‚Äô Diary), Rose Matafeo (Edinburgh Comedy Award Winner 2018), and Russell Howard (The Russell Howard Hour). Unaware of what awaits them in each wax-sealed envelope, only one competitor can become the victorious owner of His Royal Task-ness‚Äô golden head and be crowned the next Taskmaster Champion.

#Taskmaster #Comedy¬†#GregDavies #AlexHorne

snippet.title: Stadium Gameplay Trailer | Overwatch 2
snippet.description:
Forge your victory in our brand new permanent game mode, Stadium!

Strategy, teamwork, and hero evolution will determine who wins in Stadium as you and your team battle it out in this best-of-7, round-based mode.

In each round, players will be able to earn Stadium Cash that can be used to unlock powerful, game-changing abilities. Players can also take down high-value enemies marked with bounties to earn bonus Stadium Cash and turn the tide of battle.

See your hero‚Äôs upgraded abilities in action with the option to play in third-person or maintain the classic first-person perspective. The choice is yours!

Stadium also features its own standalone ranking system with season-exclusive rewards, encouraging players to master the mode and prove their competitive dominance.

Step into the arena when Season 16: Stadium launches on Apr 22.

Overwatch 2 is free to play for everyone on console & PC!
_

localized.title: Stadium Gameplay Trailer | Overwatch 2
localized.description:
Forge your victory in our brand new permanent game mode, Stadium!

Strategy, teamwork, and hero evolution will determine who wins in Stadium as you and your team battle it out in this best-of-7, round-based mode.

In each round, players will be able to earn Stadium Cash that can be used to unlock powerful, game-changing abilities. Players can also take down high-value enemies marked with bounties to earn bonus Stadium Cash and turn the tide of battle.

See your hero‚Äôs upgraded abilities in action with the option to play in third-person or maintain the classic first-person perspective. The choice is yours!

Stadium also features its own standalone ranking system with season-exclusive rewards, encouraging players to master the mode and prove their competitive dominance.

Step into the arena when Season 16: Stadium launches on Apr 22.

Overwatch 2 is free to play for everyone on console & PC!

snippet.title: 5 Lego Walkers vs 7 Obstacles
snippet.description:
5 Lego walkers are tested against different obstacles. Which one is the winner? Enjoy!

0:00 Obstacle 1: gap (10 cm)
0:27 Obstacle 2: step (2.5 cm)
0:53 Obstacle 3: drop (9 cm)
1:21 Obstacle 4: u-turn on rough surface
2:17 Obstacle 5: pillars
2:55 Obstacle 6: triangle hill (30 deg inclination)
3:40 Obstacle 7: triangle valley (35 deg inclination)

List of vehicles:
  Simple 2-legged walker (no steering)
  2-legged walker (2 legs + base for walking, a tail leg for turning)
  4-legged walker
  8-legged walker (Klann linkage)
  16-legged walker

All walkers have tennis grip on the soles of their feet.

Building 5 Lego Walkers:
https://youtu.be/LOJuK3eR8FM

snippet.title: Elephant Teaches 20 Lions That He's The King
snippet.description:
Deon Kelbrick filmed this curiously one-sided interaction and sent it to Latest Sightings. It occurred at the viewpoint on the H1-3, just north of Tshokwane Picnic Site in the Kruger National Park.

Join our channel to get access to EXTENDED and UNEDITED videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyfZleh4w7buTzi0WfY8WqA/join

Send in your wildlife video here, and earn money: https://latestsightings.com/film-earn

Deon's series of video clips began by setting the scene. A large pride of twenty lions lay spread out on the bank of a dry riverbed.

The pride consists of a mature male, several lionesses and cubs of various ages. Renowned for their strength, both individually and collectively, you would think that nothing would disturb their late morning nap.

While most of the pride rested peacefully, three of them either heard or smelt something that got their attention. Moving away from the group, they went to investigate.

Subsequently, rising up from the riverbed, appeared a young, lone elephant bull.

On reaching maturity, male elephants leave their natal herds, so this was not unusual in itself. But more about that later.

As the oversized gate-crasher came into view, the three lions tensed up. Lions are known to prey on lone elephants in some places, but seldom in Kruger Park.

And it would be no different on this day. Seeing that the bull was heading directly towards them, the three lions gave way.

It was clear that the elephant was well aware of the lions' presence. Ears flared and head held upright, the bull lengthened his stride as he made straight towards them.

When he got within twenty metres of the pride, he pulled up to assess the situation. And, to give the big cats a chance to leave of their own accord.

In response, some members of the pride got to their feet and sauntered off. Meanwhile, others remained where they were, not ready to exert themselves until the bull made his next move.

Not impressed by the lions' failure to give way immediately, the elephant took things up a notch. Showing surprising acceleration, the bull charged, trumpeting loudly as he did.

Every member of the pride, from the dominant male to the youngest cub, immediately took off in the opposite direction.

Soon enough, the elephant decided that he had made his point. Pulling up, once again, he tracked the movement of a lioness who had splintered from the pride in the chaos.

Later, satisfied that she too did not dispute his supremacy, the bull ripped up a tussock of grass to chew on.

Apparently not liking the taste of his snack, he promptly wandered off.
As for the lions, seeing their tormentor waddle off without a care in the world, they soon returned to where they had lain earlier.

If lions could talk, you can be sure none of them was about to mention anything about being 'king of the jungle'.

In both lion and elephant communities, adult males play little to no role in raising their offspring. Their contribution in this respect is limited to security and DNA. In both instances, when they reach sexual maturity, they are forced (generally by dominant males in the area) to leave their mothers.
Usually, they will band with other males to form bachelor groups or alliances, from which they derive mutual protection. This affords them an environment in which to grow stronger and wiser, thereby enhancing their chances of reproductive success when fully matured.

No doubt, this young bull's experience will have helped build his confidence, shaping his character for a long life ahead.

Contact@LatestSightings.com

localized.title: Elephant Teaches 20 Lions That He's The King
localized.description:
Deon Kelbrick filmed this curiously one-sided interaction and sent it to Latest Sightings. It occurred at the viewpoint on the H1-3, just north of Tshokwane Picnic Site in the Kruger National Park.

Join our channel to get access to EXTENDED and UNEDITED videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyfZleh4w7buTzi0WfY8WqA/join

Send in your wildlife video here, and earn money: https://latestsightings.com/film-earn

Deon's series of video clips began by setting the scene. A large pride of twenty lions lay spread out on the bank of a dry riverbed.

The pride consists of a mature male, several lionesses and cubs of various ages. Renowned for their strength, both individually and collectively, you would think that nothing would disturb their late morning nap.

While most of the pride rested peacefully, three of them either heard or smelt something that got their attention. Moving away from the group, they went to investigate.

Subsequently, rising up from the riverbed, appeared a young, lone elephant bull.

On reaching maturity, male elephants leave their natal herds, so this was not unusual in itself. But more about that later.

As the oversized gate-crasher came into view, the three lions tensed up. Lions are known to prey on lone elephants in some places, but seldom in Kruger Park.

And it would be no different on this day. Seeing that the bull was heading directly towards them, the three lions gave way.

It was clear that the elephant was well aware of the lions' presence. Ears flared and head held upright, the bull lengthened his stride as he made straight towards them.

When he got within twenty metres of the pride, he pulled up to assess the situation. And, to give the big cats a chance to leave of their own accord.

In response, some members of the pride got to their feet and sauntered off. Meanwhile, others remained where they were, not ready to exert themselves until the bull made his next move.

Not impressed by the lions' failure to give way immediately, the elephant took things up a notch. Showing surprising acceleration, the bull charged, trumpeting loudly as he did.

Every member of the pride, from the dominant male to the youngest cub, immediately took off in the opposite direction.

Soon enough, the elephant decided that he had made his point. Pulling up, once again, he tracked the movement of a lioness who had splintered from the pride in the chaos.

Later, satisfied that she too did not dispute his supremacy, the bull ripped up a tussock of grass to chew on.

Apparently not liking the taste of his snack, he promptly wandered off.
As for the lions, seeing their tormentor waddle off without a care in the world, they soon returned to where they had lain earlier.

If lions could talk, you can be sure none of them was about to mention anything about being 'king of the jungle'.

In both lion and elephant communities, adult males play little to no role in raising their offspring. Their contribution in this respect is limited to security and DNA. In both instances, when they reach sexual maturity, they are forced (generally by dominant males in the area) to leave their mothers.
Usually, they will band with other males to form bachelor groups or alliances, from which they derive mutual protection. This affords them an environment in which to grow stronger and wiser, thereby enhancing their chances of reproductive success when fully matured.

No doubt, this young bull's experience will have helped build his confidence, shaping his character for a long life ahead.

Twitter & Instagram: @LatestKruger

snippet.title: The 2025 Green Jacket Ceremony | The Masters
snippet.description:
Rory McIlroy is awarded his Green Jacket following his 2025 Masters championship victory. #themasters 

---

Since 1934, the Masters Tournament has been home to some of golf‚Äôs greatest moments. Amidst blooming azaleas, towering pines and flowering dogwoods, the first full week of April ushers in a stage unique to golf and to sport. Over four days and 72 holes, the smallest field in major championship golf competes for a chance to capture the Green Jacket and a place in Masters history.

snippet.description:

Light cast so long before sound, before song
falls on your eyes and the dance starts again

And in this grand ballroom of nothingness
your hand so warm with somethingness
we whirl and twirl and music‚Äôs invented again 
In this grand ballroom of nothingness
we soar, we sail to the only song there‚Äôs ever been: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been‚Äôs just begun: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been plays again: Love
It‚Äôs love

How marvelous just to be anything,
circling the hall to divine harmony

And in this grand ballroom of nothingness
your hand so warm with somethingness
we swirl, unfurl, and music‚Äôs invented again 
In this grand ballroom of nothingness
we soar, we sail to the only song there‚Äôs ever been: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been‚Äôs just begun: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been plays again: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been never ends: Love

And against such staggering odds of anything at all
that lonely poet Chance called the dance and built the hall 
and, with such modest hands, drew up plans and gave us all

Love

Light cast so long before sound, before song
falls on your eyes and the dance starts again

And in this grand ballroom of nothingness
your hand so warm with somethingness
we whirl and twirl and music‚Äôs invented again 
In this grand ballroom of nothingness
we soar, we sail to the only song there‚Äôs ever been: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been‚Äôs just begun: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been plays again: Love
It‚Äôs love

How marvelous just to be anything,
circling the hall to divine harmony

And in this grand ballroom of nothingness
your hand so warm with somethingness
we swirl, unfurl, and music‚Äôs invented again 
In this grand ballroom of nothingness
we soar, we sail to the only song there‚Äôs ever been: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been‚Äôs just begun: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been plays again: Love
The only song there‚Äôs ever been never ends: Love

And against such staggering odds of anything at all
that lonely poet Chance called the dance and built the hall 
and, with such modest hands, drew up plans and gave us all

Love

About A Minecraft Movie: 
From Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures and starring Jason Momoa and Jack Black, A Minecraft Movie, directed by Jared Hess, is the first ever big screen, live-action adaptation of Minecraft, the best-selling video game of all time. Welcome to the world of Minecraft, where creativity doesn't just help you craft, it's essential to one's survival! Four misfits‚ÄîGarrett "The Garbage Man" Garrison (Momoa), Henry (Hansen), Natalie (Myers) and Dawn (Brooks)‚Äîfind themselves struggling with ordinary problems when they are suddenly pulled through a mysterious portal into the Overworld: a bizarre, cubic wonderland that thrives on imagination. To get back home, they'll have to master this world (and protect it from evil things like Piglins and Zombies, too) while embarking on a magical quest with an unexpected, expert crafter, Steve (Black). Together, their adventure will challenge all five to be bold and to reconnect with the qualities that make each of them uniquely creative‚Ä¶the very skills they need to thrive back in the real world.
